<HEADLINE>
KAOHSIUNG MAYOR TO STEP UP EXHIBITION CENTER BUILDING PROJECT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan. 11 (CNA) 01/11/07  21:45:52 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
Kaohsiung Mayor Chen Chu said Thursday that she will push for the
central government to earmark NT$3 billion (US$9.15 million) for
the Kaohsiung city government to build a major international
convention and exhibition center in the southern port city.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remarks while addressing an opening ceremony for
the "2007 Information Month" show being held at the Kaohsiung
World Trade Center under the auspices of the Kaohsiung Computer
Association (KCA).
</P>
<P>
The Kaohsiung city government is stepping up various information
infrastructure projects aimed at developing Kaohsiung into a "Wi-
Fi network city" and Chen said she will seek to deliver on her
electoral campaign promise to forge an international convention
and exhibition center in Kaohsiung in four years.
</P>
<P>
KCA Chairman Wang Chun-hua noted that the "Kaohsiung Information
Month" show is the first trade show of the year, with exhibitors
showcasing their latest information technology products.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, around 250 domestic and foreign exhibitors
have set up 800 booths to display a wide variety of IT products
during the show, which will run through Jan. 16.
</P>
<P>
"Embracing digital life" is the theme of this year's exhibition,
according to which the KCA has designed various theme pavilions
at the show.
</P>
